## Editability driven by lifecycle status only (any DRAFT version is editable)

**Context**: The old rule made *older* versions read-only even when they were DRAFT — editing
was only allowed on the *latest* version. The requirement is now: editability depends solely on
the lifecycle status. **Only a DRAFT version can be edited, whatever the version is** (an older
DRAFT version is fully editable). The server-side write-gate was already status-only
(`PermissionMiddleware` blocks edits unless status == DRAFT); the "older version is read-only"
restriction lived entirely in the frontend, which keyed read-only off `is_active` (= is-latest).

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js` — read-only is now driven solely by status:
   `editable = (versionStatus === 'DRAFT')`. Dropped the `!is_active` (older-version) condition.
   Repurposed `window.isActiveVersion` to mean "editable" (DRAFT) instead of "is latest", so the
   ~40 design-surface gates that key off it allow editing of older DRAFT versions. When not
   editable, both `read-only-status` and `read-only-version` are added to `<body>` and the navbar
   note reads "This version is <STATUS> (read-only). Set it back to DRAFT to make changes."
2. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-information.js` — `updateVersionStatusUI(...)` is now fed
   `(statusData.status === 'DRAFT')` instead of `statusData.is_active`, so the Global-tab form
   fields enable for any DRAFT version.
3. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-actions.js` — `updateVersionStatus(...)` renamed its first
   param to `editable` and is fed `(data.status === 'DRAFT')`; the read-only banner message now
   says "Set it back to Draft to make changes." instead of "Load the latest version".
4. `src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js` — updated the `canEditOntology` doc comment to
   reflect that `isActiveVersion === false` now means "not editable (not DRAFT)".
5. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py` — the load-from-UC confirmation message now labels the
   loaded version by lifecycle status (`editable` vs `<STATUS>, read-only`) instead of
   `Latest`/`Read-only` based on is-latest. The create-new-version guard (must load latest first)
   is unchanged, since creating a version is a separate operation from editing.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-information.js`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-actions.js`
- `src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js`
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`

