## Fix: curated business views render empty after Back-to-Draft / on an older DRAFT version

**Context**: After sending a version Back to Draft (or loading an older version that is now
editable), the Ontology Designer canvas appeared empty for *business views* specifically — the
core ontology and the navbar were fine. Investigation confirmed there was **no server-side data
loss**: the stored views still held all entities and their `visibility.hiddenEntities` lists
(e.g. `Support` = 15 entities, 9 hidden -> 6 visible). The blank canvas was purely a client-side
render problem with two contributing causes:
1. A curated view is rendered with `center: false`, so the visible subset stayed at its original
   wide-circle positions while the now-hidden entities (which anchored the centre) were removed —
   leaving the few visible cards off-screen, i.e. an apparently empty canvas.
2. `loadOntologyIntoDesigner` entered the merge branch on `OntologyState.config` being truthy
   alone; right after a reload `config.classes` can still be empty, producing a zero-entity
   merged layout (a genuinely blank canvas).

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js` — `centerDiagram()` now computes its bounding box
   over the **visible** entities only (falling back to all when none are visible), so centring a
   curated business view frames the cards that are actually shown instead of centring around
   hidden anchors.
2. `src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js` — `loadOntologyIntoDesigner()`:
   - resolves `classes`/`properties` up-front and guards the merge branch on `classes.length > 0`
     (not just `config` truthiness), so an empty/not-yet-loaded `OntologyState` falls through to
     the saved-layout-only render instead of building a zero-entity layout;
   - both `fromJSON` calls now pass `center: _layoutHasHidden` — curated views (any hidden
     entities) are re-framed into view, while full views keep their exact saved positions.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js`
- `src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js`

**Test result**: `uv run pytest -q --ignore=tests/property --ignore=tests/e2e` -> 2532 passed,
17 skipped (frontend-only change; `tests/property` and `tests/e2e` skipped due to pre-existing
env issues: `hypothesis` not installed and a 3.9-only syntax in `tests/e2e/conftest.py`).

