## Patch six Dependabot vulnerabilities (pyarrow, starlette, aiohttp, strawberry-graphql)

**Context**: Six GitHub Dependabot alerts (#31–#36) flagged vulnerable transitive/direct
dependencies pinned in `uv.lock`. Bumped each to its first fixed release and re-resolved the
lockfile. The starlette one (BadHost / CVE-2026-48710) is the only code-relevant case: it poisons
`request.url.path` via a malformed Host header, bypassing path-based auth. The framework upgrade
fixes it, and as defense-in-depth we also switched every security-sensitive path check to read the
raw routed path (`request.scope["path"]`) per the advisory's durable-fix recommendation.

Advisories addressed:
- `pyarrow` 23.0.0 -> 23.0.1 — Arrow C++ IPC use-after-free (CVE-2026-25087 / GHSA-rgxp-2hwp-jwgg).
  The Python binding never exposed the affected `PreBufferMetadata` API; bump silences the alert (#36).
- `starlette` 0.50.0 -> 1.2.1 — BadHost missing Host-header validation (CVE-2026-48710 /
  GHSA-86qp-5c8j-p5mr) (#35). Required bumping `fastapi` (0.128.0 -> 0.136.3) for Starlette 1.0+ support.
- `aiohttp` 3.13.5 -> 3.14.0 (transitive via mlflow) — CookieJar.load() pickle RCE (CVE-2026-34993 /
  GHSA-jg22-mg44-37j8) and per-request cookie leak on cross-origin redirect (CVE-2026-47265 /
  GHSA-hg6j-4rv6-33pg) (#31, #32).
- `strawberry-graphql` 0.315.4 -> 0.316.0 — MaxAliasesLimiter fragment-spread bypass (CVE-2026-47707 /
  GHSA-fr49-mhgj-crfc) and circular-fragment DOS in QueryDepthLimiter (#33, #34).

**Changes**:
1. `pyproject.toml` — bumped direct floors `pyarrow>=23.0.1`, `starlette>=1.0.1`,
   `strawberry-graphql>=0.315.7`, `fastapi>=0.129.0`; added `aiohttp>=3.14.0` to
   `[tool.uv].constraint-dependencies` (transitive). Each pin carries a CVE/GHSA comment.
2. `uv.lock` — re-resolved (`uv lock`); 5 packages updated as listed above.
3. `src/shared/fastapi/csrf.py` — CSRF bypass-prefix check reads `request.scope["path"]`
   instead of `request.url.path` (BadHost durable fix).
4. `src/back/objects/session/FileSessionMiddleware.py` — session bypass-prefix check reads
   `request.scope["path"]`.
5. `src/shared/fastapi/main.py` — `PermissionMiddleware` permission bypass-prefix check reads
   `request.scope["path"]`.
6. `src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py` — added `_is_external_request()` helper (dedupes 4
   identical external/internal gate checks) reading `request.scope["path"]`; replaced all 4 call sites.
7. `tests/units/auth/test_permission_middleware.py` — `_make_request()` now also sets
   `req.scope = {"path": path}` so the mock mirrors a real ASGI request (the middleware reads the
   raw routed path from `scope["path"]`). Without this the mock returned a `MagicMock` for the path.

**Modified files**:
- `pyproject.toml`
- `uv.lock`
- `src/shared/fastapi/csrf.py`
- `src/back/objects/session/FileSessionMiddleware.py`
- `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`
- `src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py`
- `tests/units/auth/test_permission_middleware.py`

**Test result**: full suite `uv run pytest -q` -> **2771 passed, 17 skipped, 41 failed**. The 41
failures are pre-existing and unrelated: the `tests/mcp/integration` suite leaves the asyncio event
loop closed, cascading into the async endpoint tests (`test_review_endpoints.py`,
`test_set_version_status_endpoint.py`) — both confirmed **12 passed** in isolation. The 195
`test_permission_middleware.py` tests pass after the `scope` fix.

