## Business Views: count and group from *visible* entities, not the full ontology

**Context**: In the Visual Ontology Designer (Business Views) the entity counter showed the total
number of ontology classes merged into the layout rather than the entities actually visible in the
curated view. A `Support` view with 6 visible entities (9 hidden) displayed "Entities: 15", and
clicking *Create Group* proposed all 15 entities instead of the 6 belonging to the view. A view
stores every ontology class in `layout.entities[]` and hides the non-members via
`visibility.hiddenEntities`, so any counter built from `entities.size` over-counts.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js`
   - Added `getVisibleEntityCount()`, `getVisibleRelationshipCount()`,
     `getVisibleInheritanceCount()`, and `getVisibleEntityNames()` helpers that respect
     `visibilityState`. The relationship/inheritance counters apply the full visibility rule
     (`sourceVisible && targetVisible && explicitlyVisible`), mirroring
     `_updateRelationshipVisibility` / `_updateInheritanceVisibility`, so links whose endpoint
     entities are hidden are not counted.
   - `_updateStatusBar()` now reports the visible counts (headline now matches the canvas).
   - Visibility palette section title now shows "Entities (visible / total visible)".
   - `_toggleItemVisibility()` refreshes the status bar so counters stay live when entities are
     shown/hidden or "Hide from view" is used.
2. `src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js`
   - `createGroupFromView()` now builds group members from `getVisibleEntityNames()` (visible-only),
     with a graceful fallback to the previous full list if the helper is unavailable.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js`
- `src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js`

**Test result**: `uv run pytest -q` -> **2771 passed, 17 skipped, 41 failed** in 256.62s. The 41
failures are the same pre-existing, unrelated set documented in earlier sections of this file
(`tests/mcp/integration` leaves the asyncio event loop closed, cascading into
`test_review_endpoints.py` / `test_set_version_status_endpoint.py`). This change is frontend-only
(OntoViz canvas JS), which has no Python test coverage, so the failing set is unchanged by it.
